Blooming of blue-green algae, especially the toxigenic species Nodularia spumigena, occurs annually in the Baltic Sea region, presenting a threat for animals exposed to contaminated water. Previously, the identification of blue-green algal toxin was laborious, requiring water samples and the use of experimental animals;
5,6,10,16,25,26
 algal toxins have not been analyzed routinely from animal tissues in diagnostic cases. In this report, blue-green algal toxicosis was confirmed by direct toxin analysis from organ samples.
